cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses reinforcement learning in robotics applications, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on designing policies using a maximum entropy algorithm. The second most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper specifically mentions robotics applications. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper introduces and extends the idea of robust stability and $H_\infty$ control. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning in robotics. The fifth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper mentions the use of a sample-based approach for analyzing the Lyapunov stability and performance robustness of a learning-based control system.
